Remove three buttons from Firefox's default toolbar placements:

  - fxa-toolbar-menu-button   ("Account" / Sync menu)
  - firefox-view-button       ("View recent browsing across windows…")
  - alltabs-button            ("List all tabs")

Gjoa's tab tree (sidebar) is the primary navigation surface; the
horizontal account/firefox-view/all-tabs buttons are redundant clutter
in this layout. Users who want them back can re-add via the toolbar
customization panel (right-click toolbar → Customize Toolbar).

Three placement arrays touched:
  - navbarPlacements                         (default nav bar)
  - verticalTabsDefaultPlacements (NAVBAR)   (when vertical tabs on)
  - AREA_TABSTRIP defaultPlacements          (horizontal tab strip)

diff --git a/browser/components/customizableui/CustomizableUI.sys.mjs b/browser/components/customizableui/CustomizableUI.sys.mjs
